title: Record PGA ticket sales for Whistling Straits bode well for economy
text:
Record PGA ticket sales for Whistling Straits bode well for economy Aug 3, 2015, 7:13am CDT Industries & Tags Enlarge The trophy from the PGA Championship, which will be held at Whistling Straits in Kohlerâ€¦ more The PGA Championship golf tournament to be held at Whistling Straits next week is already the highest-grossing of the event's 97-year history, which coupled with two previously successful tournaments at the Sheboygan County course, is good news for local businesses. Hotels rooms in Sheboygan County have been filled for a year and the demand for rooms will likely spillover into nearby cities like Fond du Lac, Manitowoc, Milwaukee and Green Bay. The benefits are also expected to extend to restaurants and other attractions near hotels and travel routes. The PGA Championship has an economic impact of more than $100 million.
